{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/F5Networks/terraform-provider-bigip/pulls/1165","id":3764760531,"node_id":"PR_kwDOCPfthM7gZa_T","html_url":"https://github.com/F5Networks/terraform-provider-bigip/pull/1165","diff_url":"https://github.com/F5Networks/terraform-provider-bigip/pull/1165.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/F5Networks/terraform-provider-bigip/pull/1165.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/F5Networks/terraform-provider-bigip/issues/1165","number":1165,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"Fix clearing all records on an existing bigip_ltm_datagroup (#1164)","user":{"login":"mdkent","id":71034,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcxMDM0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/71034?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdkent","html_url":"https://github.com/mdkent","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdkent/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdkent/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdkent/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdkent/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdkent/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdkent/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdkent/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdkent/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mdkent/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"## Summary\n- Drop `omitempty` from `Records` on the vendored `dataGroupDTO` so a PUT with an empty record set actually sends `\"records\": []` to BigIP. With `omitempty`, both `nil` and `[]` were stripped and BigIP kept the existing records.\n- `resource_bigip_ltm_datagroup.go` now initializes `records` as `[]bigip.DataGroupRecord{}` (instead of leaving it nil) so an empty record set serializes as `[]` rather than `null`. Simplifies the create/update paths slightly.\n- Adds `TestAccBigipLtmDataGroup_Update_ClearRecords`, a two-step acceptance test that creates a data group with two records and then applies an empty config — asserting the live BigIP record count goes from 2 → 0 while the data group itself survives.\n\nFixes #1164\n\n## Test plan\n- [ ] `go build ./...` (passes locally)\n- [ ] `go vet ./...` (passes locally)\n- [ ] `TF_ACC=1 go test ./bigip/ -run TestAccBigipLtmDataGroup_Update_ClearRecords -v` against a live BigIP\n\n## Note on the vendor change\nThe actual on-the-wire fix lives in `vendor/github.com/f5devcentral/go-bigip/ltm.go`. The matching upstream PR is [f5devcentral/go-bigip#132](https://github.com/f5devcentral/go-bigip/pull/132) — landing that means the next `go mod vendor` won't revert the fix here.\n","created_at":"2026-05-28T20:37:28Z","updated_at":"2026-06-03T23:50:04Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"ad0d0e4da95f6dd91b3e0717f9ae5f923432bc10","assignees":[],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[],"milestone":null,"draft":false,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/F5Networks/terraform-provider-bigip/pulls/1165/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/F5Networks/terraform-provider-bigip/pulls/1165/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/F5Networks/terraform-provider-bigip/pulls/comments{/number}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/F5Networks/terraform-provider-bigip/issues/1165/comments","statuses_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/F5Networks/terraform-provider-bigip/statuses/e51587028b067004913d2e3ecb27360a0b6dff48","head":{"label":"basecamp:ltm-datagroup-empty","ref":"ltm-datagroup-empty","sha":"e51587028b067004913d2e3ecb27360a0b6dff48","user":{"login":"basecamp","id":13131,"node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjEzMTMx","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/13131?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/basecamp","html_url":"https://github.com/basecamp","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/